roots.book.herblore_book.intro.title=Tome of Herblore
roots.book.herblore_book.intro.desc=Within this tome is contained the ancient art of herblore. It bears a listing of the great mystical herbs, their properties, and a description of their synthesis under the moonlight.
roots.book.herblore_book.contents.title=Contents
roots.book.herblore_book.contents.desc=
roots.book.herblore_book.straw.title=Straw
roots.book.herblore_book.straw.desc=Straw, the dried and dead form of grass. This hollow substance has none of the life it previously had, nor does it have inherent magical prowess. However, it is a fine material for certain building blocks.
roots.book.herblore_book.thatch.title=Thatch
roots.book.herblore_book.thatch.desc=A mass of compounded and tangled straw. It makes a fine roof.
roots.book.herblore_book.moonlight_circle.title=Moonlight Circle
roots.book.herblore_book.moonlight_circle.desc=Circles of mossy standing stones may be found. There are small markings on the ground within the circle, four smaller marks and a central symbol. Grow one plant on the central rune, and four other plants on the smaller markings, and a wholly new plant may be grown. Any crops used must be at maximum growth.
roots.book.herblore_book.wildroot.title=Wildroot
roots.book.herblore_book.wildroot.desc=Grown under moonlight. Represents capacitance and energy.
roots.book.herblore_book.moonglow.title=Moonglow
roots.book.herblore_book.moonglow.desc=Grown under moonlight. Represents mysticism and the cosmic. 
roots.book.herblore_book.terra_moss.title=Terra Moss
roots.book.herblore_book.terra_moss.desc=Grown under moonlight. Represents life, plants, and growth.
roots.book.herblore_book.pereskia_flower.title=Pereskia Blossom
roots.book.herblore_book.pereskia_flower.desc=Grown under moonlight. Represents freedom and flow.
roots.book.herblore_book.aubergine.title=Aubergine
roots.book.herblore_book.aubergine.desc=Grown under moonlight. Represents purity, natural order.
roots.book.herblore_book.spirit_herb.title=Spirit Herb
roots.book.herblore_book.spirit_herb.desc=Grown under moonlight. Represents inner strength, vitality, and souls. Must be grown on soul sand.
roots.book.herblore_book.wood_shears.title=Wooden Shears
roots.book.herblore_book.wood_shears.desc=A key tool for the herbologist. Allows safe harvest of natural plants.
roots.book.herblore_book.wood_knife.title=Knives
roots.book.herblore_book.wood_knife.desc=A quick weapon, useful for harvesting bark when breaking logs. Can be made out of other mundane tool materials.
roots.book.herblore_book.wood_hammer.title=Hammers
roots.book.herblore_book.wood_hammer.desc=A slow weapon, able to crush some materials into dust. Can be made out of other mundane tool materials.
roots.book.herblore_book.firestarter.title=Firestarter
roots.book.herblore_book.firestarter.desc=Simple firestarter, for lighting fires or igniting the pyre.
roots.book.herblore_book.pyre.title=Pyre
roots.book.herblore_book.pyre.desc=Mystical bonfire. Further use is detailed on the following page.
roots.book.herblore_book.pyre_info.title=Pyre Rituals
roots.book.herblore_book.pyre_info.desc=The pyre is the core of ritual magic. Magical herbs and items may be placed atop it, or dropped onto it if alike materials are already present. When the pyre is lit, and any requirements on the ritual's activation are met, a ritual will commence.
roots.book.herblore_book.dwindle_dust.title=Dwindle Dust
roots.book.herblore_book.dwindle_dust.desc=Festering ash from a smashed evil skull. Used in dark magic.
roots.book.herblore_book.totem_fragment.title=Totem Fragments
roots.book.herblore_book.totem_fragment.desc=Fragmented material from a smashed mystical object. Contains the essence of immortality.
roots.book.herblore_book.runestone.title=Runestone
roots.book.herblore_book.runestone.desc=Blued stone, forged by throwing stone onto the central symbol of a moonlight circle. It bears slight magical properties, and can be carved and chiseled into several forms, detailed in the following pages.
roots.book.herblore_book.runestone_brick.title=Runestone Bricks
roots.book.herblore_book.runestone_brick.desc=Simple bricks of runestone.
roots.book.herblore_book.chiseled_runestone.title=Chiseled Runestone
roots.book.herblore_book.chiseled_runestone.desc=Runestone with a sigil carved into each of its faces. It has some use in channeling natural power.

roots.book.spellcraft_book.intro.title=Tome of Spellcraft
roots.book.spellcraft_book.intro.desc=Within this tome is contained the ancient power of spellcraft. It bears a description of the method by which spells can be cast, a listing of known spells, and a description of their abilities.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.contents.title=Contents
roots.book.spellcraft_book.contents.desc=
roots.book.spellcraft_book.mortar.title=Mortar
roots.book.spellcraft_book.mortar.desc=Hewn of gray stone, the mortar is used with the pestle to grind objects.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.pestle.title=Pestle
roots.book.spellcraft_book.pestle.desc=Hewn of white stone, the pestle is used with the mortar to grind objects.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.pouch.title=Herbal Pouch
roots.book.spellcraft_book.pouch.desc=The herbal pouch makes a fine container for herbal powder.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.pouch_fill.title=Herbal Powder
roots.book.spellcraft_book.pouch_fill.desc=The pestle can be used to grind up herbs, to be contained within a pouch.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.staff.title=Staff
roots.book.spellcraft_book.staff.desc=Infusing raw wood with two of any magical herb, a mystical staff may be created.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.imbuer.title=Imbuer
roots.book.spellcraft_book.imbuer.desc=This construct of wood and stone can imbue a petal dust spell into the current slot of a staff.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.spellcraft.title=Spell Creation
roots.book.spellcraft_book.spellcraft.desc=Spells must be cast from one of the four slots of a staff. A mortar and pestle must be used to create petal dust from a certain combination of items. Then, the dust must be imbued into the staff, binding the currently selected slot of the staff to that spell.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.casting.title=Casting
roots.book.spellcraft_book.casting.desc=After a spell has been imbued, it must be provided reagents via herbal powder within pouches from the caster's inventory. A spell will either consume the cost instantly, creating an effect, or will consume the cost slowly over time, producing a continuous effect. A staff must recharge briefly after the casting of any spell is completed.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.orange_tulip.title=Spell: Wildfire
roots.book.spellcraft_book.orange_tulip.desc=Spews forth a jet of fire from the tip of the staff.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.dandelion.title=Spell: Dandelion Winds
roots.book.spellcraft_book.dandelion.desc=Blasts forth a massive blast of wind that blows away creatures before the caster.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.allium.title=Spell: Acid Cloud
roots.book.spellcraft_book.allium.desc=Conjures up a ring of burning gas around the caster.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.azure_bluet.title=Spell: Shatter
roots.book.spellcraft_book.azure_bluet.desc=Fires a beam of force into a targeted block nearby, instantly breaking it apart.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.red_tulip.title=Spell: Sanctuary
roots.book.spellcraft_book.red_tulip.desc=Brings forth a sphere of shielding around the caster, forcing away creatures and projectiles.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.rose.title=Spell: Rose's Thorns
roots.book.spellcraft_book.rose.desc=Throws a ball of glowing thorns forward. Upon landing, the ball of thorns will create a trap that will harm any creature that steps on it.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.blue_orchid.title=Spell: Gravity Boost
roots.book.spellcraft_book.blue_orchid.desc=Propels the caster forward, allowing them to leave the earth and briefly soar to a destination.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.lilac.title=Spell: Growth Infusion
roots.book.spellcraft_book.lilac.desc=Imbues the targeted block with life, causing vastly accelerated growth.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.peony.title=Spell: Petal Shell
roots.book.spellcraft_book.peony.desc=Can conjure up to three petals about the caster. Each petal can absorb one strike.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.poppy.title=Spell: Mind Ward
roots.book.spellcraft_book.poppy.desc=Creates a floating ward above the creature the caster targets, preventing them from attacking the caster.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.pink_tulip.title=Spell: Life Drain
roots.book.spellcraft_book.pink_tulip.desc=Drains life from all creatures within a range in front of the caster.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.white_tulip.title=Spell: Light Drifter
roots.book.spellcraft_book.white_tulip.desc=Allows the caster to become ethereal, passing through solid objects, for a time.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.sunflower.title=Spell: Radiance
roots.book.spellcraft_book.sunflower.desc=Radiates a tremendous beam of golden light from the tip of the staff. The scourge of the undead.
roots.book.spellcraft_book.oxeye_daisy.title=Spell: Time Stop
roots.book.spellcraft_book.oxeye_daisy.desc=Prevents time from progressing in a region around where the spell is cast, for all creatures besides the caster.

roots.book.ritual_book.intro.title=Tome of Natural Arts
roots.book.ritual_book.intro.desc=Within this tome is contained the knowledge of the natural arts, the great rites of power, and various mystic elements of the world.
roots.book.ritual_book.contents.title=Contents
roots.book.ritual_book.contents.desc=
roots.book.ritual_book.fairy_pools.title=Fairy Circles
roots.book.ritual_book.fairy_pools.desc=If in your travels you happen across a circle of birch and oak about a shallow pond, take note: such an occurrence is often the sign of a fairy circle. At night these circles come to life with all manner of fairies, glittering in the darkness above the pool.
roots.book.ritual_book.fairy_dust.title=Fairy Dust
roots.book.ritual_book.fairy_dust.desc=Dropped from slain fairies, fairy dust possessed myriad mystical powers. The most immediate of these is its luminance: placing a pile of fairy dust on the ground will create a glowing multicolored light.
roots.book.ritual_book.standing_stones.title=Standing Stones
roots.book.ritual_book.standing_stones.desc=Several powerful rituals require additional measures to keep their magic under a druid's control. In these cases, standing stones are required. Each stone consists of several pieces of ordinary Runestone, capped with a block of Chiseled Runestone. When these stones are necessary, the specific standing stones required and their sizes will be listed in this book.
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_life.title=Ritual of Life
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_life.desc=Cast in a grove of at least four birch trees. Will regenerate the vitality of nearby creatures, and boost the growth of nearby crops.
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_storm.title=Rite of the Storm
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_storm.desc=Invokes a torrent of rain from the heavens, and keeps fire at bay for all creatures within its radius.
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_light.title=Ritual of Light
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_light.desc=Cast during the day. Will banish the rain, make days longer and nights shorter while active, and burn foul undead in its vicinity.
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_regrowth.title=Rite of Regrowth
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_regrowth.desc=Will grow out existing groves of trees into forests, and grow grass and flowers on barren earth.
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_fire_storm.title=Storm of Fire
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_fire_storm.desc=Perform in a circle of three standing stones, each three meters high. Rains down fire from the skies.
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_windwall.title=Wall of the Winds
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_windwall.desc=Forces away all creatures with a mark of evil with a powerful gust of wind.
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_warden.title=Ritual of the Warden
roots.book.ritual_book.ritual_warden.desc=Perform in a circle of standing stones, with three that are three meters high, and three that are four meters high. Prevents all injury to creatures near it.
roots.book.ritual_book.offertory_plate.title=Offertory Plate
roots.book.ritual_book.offertory_plate.desc=Can be placed near a fairy circle to offer herbs to the fairies. Details on following page.
roots.book.ritual_book.offertory_plate_info.title=Offering Details
roots.book.ritual_book.offertory_plate_info.desc=Fairies will accept a variety of offerings. In order of value, mundane crops, mystical herbs, and rare monster remains may be sacrificed. Once per day, the fairies will exchange offerings for an amount of fairy dust depending on the value and quantity of the offering. Occasionally they may even give you a Fairy Charm.
roots.book.ritual_book.fairy_charm.title=Fairy Charm
roots.book.ritual_book.fairy_charm.desc=A rare reward in return for an offering, Fairy Charms may be received on Offertory Plates. Offering a Charm to a fairy as an active friendship will spark a bond between you and the sprite, and it will follow you as a companion. Tamed fairies may be right-clicked to toggle their close following.

